issues.body:
Resource server providing informative authorization_details body SHOULD also provide a **stable reference**, guiding client on token selection.
```
{
  **"authorization_hint": [hash or id]**,
  "authorization_details": [{
    "type": "payment_initiation",
    "instructedAmount": {
      "currency": "EUR",
      "amount": "100.00"
    },
    "creditorAccount": {
      "iban": "DE02120300000000202051"
    }
  }]
}
```

As Resource server is the one deciding on token's usage semantics (single / multi usage), it makes sense that alongside providing informative authorization_details body it SHALL also provide an indication to client on the usage of the resulting token

{
  **"token_usage": “single / multi / n (3)”**,
  "authorization_details": [{
    "type": "payment_initiation",
    "instructedAmount": {
      "currency": "EUR",
      "amount": "100.00"
    },
    "creditorAccount": {
      "iban": "DE02120300000000202051"
    }
  }]
}
